{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XWxACD3eZxSoU1P64gfkQR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Iteration 17 → 18 Improvement Plan\n     2→\n     3→## Failure summary\n     4→\n     5→| File | Expected | Got | Root cause |\n     6→|------|----------|-----|------------|\n     7→| Faszerowana papryka.real.txt | Faszerowana papryka | WARZYWA | ALL_CAPS category footer bypasses filters, wins on bonus |\n     8→\n     9→---\n    10→\n    11→## Root cause analysis\n    12→\n    13→### RC-1: `SECTION_LABELS` missing Polish food-category chapter headers\n    14→\n    15→\"WARZYWA\" (vegetables) is a chapter/category divider in a recipe book — structurally identical to \"SKŁADNIKI\" (ingredients) or \"PRZYGOTOWANIE\" (preparation), but from a different vocabulary. The current `SECTION_LABELS` set covers *recipe-internal* section labels (ingredients, instructions, tips) but not *book-level* category labels (vegetables, meats, soups, desserts).\n    16→\n    17→These category labels appear as ALL_CAPS single words at page boundaries (typically last or first line). They are never recipe titles.\n    18→\n    19→### RC-2: Multi-title guard collapses to highest score without positional awareness\n    20→\n    21→When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives alongside mixed-case candidates, the guard picks the highest scorer unconditionally (line 738):\n    22→\n    23→```typescript\n    24→} else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n    25→  selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n    26→}\n    27→```\n    28→\n    29→This conflates two situations:\n    30→- ALL_CAPS is the real title → collapse is correct\n    31→- ALL_CAPS is a footer/category label that scored marginally higher due to bonus → collapse is wrong\n    32→\n    33→The guard has no concept of document structure: a label on the last line of the document (after all recipe content) should not beat a title on line 0.\n    34→\n    35→### RC-3: `allCapsBonus` applies unconditionally to single-word ALL_CAPS\n    36→\n    37→The +0.08 `allCapsBonus` fires for any ALL_CAPS text with ≥4 alpha characters (line 499). Single-word ALL_CAPS terms like `WARZYWA` receive the full bonus despite being ineligible for the `isStructuralHeading` slot (which requires ≥2 words). This amplifies weak category-label candidates enough to overtake legitimate titles.\n    38→\n    39→### Common theme\n    40→\n    41→All three root causes share one failure mode: **the ALL_CAPS preference system elevates vocabulary-category labels that are structurally indistinguishable from titles under current filters**. The actual title — on line 0 with strong positional signal — loses because the algorithm's ALL_CAPS bias is unguarded against labels appearing after body content.\n    42→\n    43→---\n    44→\n    45→## Proposed changes\n    46→\n    47→### Change 1: Expand `SECTION_LABELS` with Polish food-category labels\n    48→\n    49→**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` — `SECTION_LABELS` set\n    50→\n    51→**What:** Add common Polish recipe-book chapter/category headers (stored without diacritics, matching existing convention).\n    52→\n    53→**Before:**\n    54→```typescript\n    55→const SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n    56→  // English\n    57→  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n    58→  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n    59→  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n    60→  // Polish (stored without diacritics for OCR resilience)\n    61→  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n    62→  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n    63→  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n    64→]);\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→**After:**\n    68→```typescript\n    69→const SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n    70→  // English\n    71→  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n    72→  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n    73→  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n    74→  // Polish — recipe section labels (stored without diacritics for OCR resilience)\n    75→  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n    76→  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n    77→  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n    78→  // Polish — recipe-book chapter/category labels (food groups, meal types)\n    79→  \"warzywa\",          // vegetables\n    80→  \"mieso\",            // meat (mięso)\n    81→  \"miesa\",            // meats (mięsa)\n    82→  \"ryby\",             // fish\n    83→  \"owoce morza\",      // seafood\n    84→  \"zupy\",             // soups\n    85→  \"salatki\",          // salads (sałatki)\n    86→  \"desery\",           // desserts\n    87→  \"napoje\",           // drinks\n    88→  \"pieczywo\",         // bread/baked goods\n    89→  \"przekaski\",        // appetizers/snacks\n    90→  \"sniadania\",        // breakfasts (śniadania)\n    91→  \"obiady\",           // dinners/lunches\n    92→  \"kolacje\",          // suppers\n    93→  \"makarony\",         // pasta dishes\n    94→  \"kasza\",            // groats/grains\n    95→  \"kasze\",            // groats/grains (plural)\n    96→  \"dania glowne\",     // main courses (dania główne)\n    97→  \"przystawki\",       // starters\n    98→  \"dodatki\",          // side dishes\n    99→  \"przetwory\",        // preserves\n   100→  \"wypieki\",          // baked goods\n   101→  \"ciasta\",           // cakes (plural)\n   102→  \"ciastka\",          // cookies\n   103→  \"torty\",            // layer cakes\n   104→  \"placki\",           // pancakes/flatbreads\n   105→  \"koktajle\",         // cocktails/smoothies\n   106→]);\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→**Why this works:** Directly catches `WARZYWA` (normalized to `warzywa`) at the hard-filter stage. It never becomes a candidate, so the downstream scoring and guard logic never sees it.\n   110→\n   111→**Risk:** Extremely low. These are generic food-category words, not dish names. No legitimate recipe title is just \"WARZYWA\" or \"ZUPY\".\n   112→\n   113→### Change 2: Position-aware single-ALL_CAPS guard\n   114→\n   115→**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` — multi-title guard block (~line 737)\n   116→\n   117→**What:** When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives alongside mixed-case candidates, check whether the ALL_CAPS candidate appears in the last 25% of the document. If so, prefer the highest-scoring candidate from the first half of the document instead. This catches category footers that slip past `SECTION_LABELS`.\n   118→\n   119→**Before:**\n   120→```typescript\n   121→} else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   122→  selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   123→}\n   124→```\n   125→\n   126→**After:**\n   127→```typescript\n   128→} else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   129→  const theCapCandidate = allCapsSelected[0];\n   130→  const capRelPos = theCapCandidate.position / lines.length;\n   131→  // If the sole ALL_CAPS candidate is in the last 25% of the document,\n   132→  // it's likely a category footer, not a title. Prefer the best earlier candidate.\n   133→  if (capRelPos > 0.75) {\n   134→    const earlierCandidates = selected.filter(\n   135→      (s) => s.position / lines.length <= 0.75\n   136→    );\n   137→    if (earlierCandidates.length > 0) {\n   138→      selected = [earlierCandidates.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   139→    } else {\n   140→      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   141→    }\n   142→  } else {\n   143→    selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   144→  }\n   145→}\n   146→```\n   147→\n   148→**Why this works:** Recipe titles appear at or near the top of the page. A single ALL_CAPS word at the very end of a recipe page (after ingredients and instructions) is almost always a section/category marker for the next chapter. This heuristic provides a structural safety net for category labels not in `SECTION_LABELS`.\n   149→\n   150→**Risk:** Low. Legitimate ALL_CAPS titles at position >75% are rare — recipe titles appear at the top, not the bottom. Even if such a case exists, the candidate would need to be the *sole* ALL_CAPS survivor AND be competing with mixed-case candidates to trigger this path.\n   151→\n   152→### Change 3: Reduce `allCapsBonus` for single-word candidates\n   153→\n   154→**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` — allCapsBonus computation (~line 499)\n   155→\n   156→**What:** Reduce the ALL_CAPS bonus from +0.08 to +0.03 for single-word candidates. Multi-word ALL_CAPS candidates keep the full +0.08.\n   157→\n   158→**Before:**\n   159→```typescript\n   160→const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   161→  ? 0.08\n   162→  : 0;\n   163→```\n   164→\n   165→**After:**\n   166→```typescript\n   167→const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   168→  ? (wordCount(rs.text) >= 2 ? 0.08 : 0.03)\n   169→  : 0;\n   170→```\n   171→\n   172→**Why this works:** Single-word ALL_CAPS terms are overwhelmingly section/category labels, not recipe titles. Real recipe titles in ALL_CAPS are almost always multi-word (\"KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA\", \"LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS\"). Reducing the bonus for single words narrows the score gap between `WARZYWA` (+0.03) and `Faszerowana papryka` (no bonus but position factor ~1.12×), making the position factor decisive.\n   173→\n   174→**Risk:** Low-moderate. If a legitimate single-word ALL_CAPS recipe title exists (e.g., \"TZATZIKI\"), it would still get +0.03 bonus plus potential structural heading bonus if applicable. The reduction from 0.08 to 0.03 is small enough that a genuinely title-like embedding score would still win.\n   175→\n   176→---\n   177→\n   178→## Defense-in-depth analysis\n   179→\n   180→These three changes form concentric defensive layers:\n   181→\n   182→| Layer | What it catches | When it fires |\n   183→|-------|----------------|---------------|\n   184→| **Change 1** (SECTION_LABELS) | Known Polish category labels | Hard filter — before scoring |\n   185→| **Change 3** (reduced bonus) | Unknown single-word ALL_CAPS labels | Scoring — reduces their competitive edge |\n   186→| **Change 2** (position guard) | Any ALL_CAPS footer that slips through | Multi-title guard — last-resort structural check |\n   187→\n   188→For the `WARZYWA` case, Change 1 alone is sufficient. Changes 2 and 3 provide safety against future category labels not in the set (e.g., regional or specialized recipe-book sections).\n   189→\n   190→---\n   191→\n   192→## Expected impact\n   193→\n   194→| Metric | Before | After |\n   195→|--------|--------|-------|\n   196→| Faszerowana papryka | FAIL (`WARZYWA`) | PASS (`Faszerowana papryka`) |\n   197→| All other 10 recipes | PASS | PASS (no regression expected) |\n   198→| **Accuracy** | **90.9% (10/11)** | **100% (11/11)** |\n   199→\n   200→### Regression risk assessment\n   201→\n   202→- **KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA** (multi-word ALL_CAPS title): Unaffected — multi-word candidates keep full +0.08 bonus; position is early in document.\n   203→- **LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS** (multi-word ALL_CAPS title): Unaffected — same reasons.\n   204→- **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** (contains \"WARZYWAMI\"): Unaffected — \"WARZYWAMI\" ≠ \"WARZYWA\" and appears as part of multi-word title, not standalone.\n   205→- **Bilingual recipes** (Smażona zielona fasolka): Unaffected — translation detection runs independently of these changes.\n   206→\n   207→### What could still fail in the future\n   208→\n   209→- **Uncommon Polish category labels** not in the expanded set (e.g., \"GRZYBY\" = mushrooms, \"JAJKA\" = eggs). Mitigation: Change 2 (position guard) catches these structurally.\n   210→- **Recipe titles that are also food categories** (e.g., a recipe simply called \"Zupy\" for a specific soup). Mitigation: extremely unlikely — recipe titles are specific dish names, not generic food categories. If it does happen, the title would need to be ALL_CAPS + single word + in the last 25% of the page to be incorrectly filtered, which is an unlikely combination.\n   211→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01B9mmEi8qfo8oyEgtbdy1Qr","session_id":"2617d3ab-3f0d-4718-9e19-762421887a81","uuid":"34c16541-5fa2-4130-9167-30b97c8a4002"}
